ce:section.ce:para:
To evaluate the selective recognition ability of the new sensor, five chemical reagents with similar structure or functional groups to BPS were selected as competitors. The imprinted sensor was exposed in 0.1 M CBS (pH 5.0) containing 10 μM BPS in the presence of the analogues (bisphenol A, sulfanilic acid, hydroquinone, p-nitrophenol, 2,5-diaminophenol) at equivalent concentration as BPS. According to the experimental results (Fig. 11
                        ), it was not difficult to find that compounds with the similar structure had no considerable effect on the performance of proposed sensor for the detection of BPS. In addition, the interference of 500-fold glucose, L-phenylalanine, L-cysteine and common ions (Na+, Cu2+, K+, Zn2+ and NH4
                        +) on the sensor were also evaluated. They had little effect on the BPS reduction current.
